  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Achieving self-sufficient farming cooperatives in Makamba and Matana Diocese, Burundi</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The main objective was to increase maize production and to help the cooperative members to move from a subsistence farming model towards a business model of agriculture. They have been supported in getting access to land, selected seeds, fertilizers and livestock to provide organic manure. They have also been provided with processing units, storage rooms and capacity building training. Hence the cooperatives are now at a mature stage and are almost ready to become fully sustainable without further external intervention from Christian Aid. which will allow Christian Aid to support other communities. However, before we exit these three Cooperatives, we still need to support them in some keys activities to guarantee the sustainability of our interventions even after the funding ends. Here below are some key activities in which they need support before we exit those communities.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">the significant change we are targeting is to  keep the smallholders maize cooperative to become more viable business  entities  and self- autonomy</narrative>
  </description>
